To create a thread in C, you can use the pthread_create function. Here’s an example: 
```c
#include <pthread.h>
void* threadFunction(void* args) {
    // Thread code goes here
}
int main() {
    pthread_t thread;
    pthread_create(&thread, NULL, threadFunction, NULL);
    pthread_join(thread, NULL);
    return 0;
}
```
